algorithms.connected

Interface IConnectedValuesGroupFinder

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConnectedValuesGroupFinder, ConnectedValuesGroupFinder2

    public interface IConnectedValuesGroupFinder
    given a set of points, finds the connected among them and places them into groups. note that connected here means adjacent to one another and adjacent is defined by the default "4 neighbor" offsets, but can be overridden to use all 8 neighbors.
    Author:
    nichole

      • findGroups

        java.util.List<gnu.trove.set.TLongSet> findGroups(int[][] data)
        find the groups of connected points in pixIdxs where connected means is adjacent to another point in the group and having this pixelValue. The adjacency by default is using the 4 neighbor pattern search unless the user has set that to 8 neighbors. The runtime complexity is essentially O(pixIdxs.size()).

        data -
